cs.SI, cs.SNA, cs.DL, cs.CYBER, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper uses network analysis to explore the links between economic journals based on the interlocking editorship. 
2. cs.SNA (Social Network Analysis) - The paper's main focus is on analyzing the structure of the network generated by interlocking editorship. 
3. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) - The paper uses a database of all editors of ECONLIT journals to conduct the analysis. 
4. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) - Although not the main focus, the paper touches upon the power dynamics of editors in defining the editorial policy of their journals, which could be relevant to cybersecurity. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses network analysis as a tool to explore the structure of the interlocking editorship network.
